Use algebraic and graphical strategies to make use of structure with quadratic, polynomial, and rational functions to solve real-world problems, including but not limited to:
a. Completing the square to rewrite contextual quadratic functions in vertex form and interpret the outcome;
b. Determining the number of solutions to a function using graphical and algebraic forms (including the discriminant and complex numbers as appropriate);
c. Factoring, grouping, and rewriting functions using properties of exponents; and
d. Identifying and explaining extraneous roots.

